Vice President Mike Pence has appointed Jarrod Agen as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of Communications to the Vice President. Agen brings over 15 years of experience in federal and state government, media relations, international affairs, and conservative politics. He has worked in various roles at the U.S. Department of Homeland Security, the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, and the U.S. Department of State. Agen also served as Chief of Staff for Governor Rick Snyder of Michigan during the Flint water crisis. He has previously worked for Mayor Rudy Giuliani, Sharron Angle, and Steve Poizner, and started his career at MSNBC.